      },
      "date": "2018-11-07 21:22:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nArshad, in the future, only patches that are strictly changing whitespace should use the trivial keyword. Changes that change code functionality should run a full set of tests. That is fine because there is no rush to land these patches, and they can wait a few extra hours to finish testing.",
