        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-11-07 22:11:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2\n\n> I see what happened. Someone  failed their math exam :-( See\n > MGC_IDX_LEN voodoo.\n\nNo, I think that part is correct. \"sizeof(static_string)\" includes the trailing NUL. John points out that the target_name2index() change no longer updates endptr, which is an argument that the caller needs to work properly.\n\nI'm going to land this, to get testing working again. I'd suggest to drop the use of kstrtoul() from the new version of this patch (along with other non-whitespace changes), and keep simple_strtoul() since it does what we want.\n\n In the future, only use trivial for whitespace and comment changes, and put functional changes into a separate patch that runs normal testing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
